Elements

Defendant Laura M. Gibson in court (in custody) with attorney William R. F. Ackell. 
John P Snider appeared for the State of Wisconsin. 
Plea Questionnaire / Waiver of Rights filed with the Court. 
Defendant enters guilty plea to Count 1 in 16CM72, Count 1 in 16CM257, and Counts 1, 7 & 8 in 16CM321. 
Rights explained. 
Court accepts pleas and finds defendant guilty. 
All remaining counts are dismissed and read in. 
Court orders sentence withheld, probation 2 years concurrent. 
Conditions: 
- pay costs, including DOMAB 
- pay restitution/surcharge per summary (16CM321) 
- submit to assessments/counseling and abide by recommendations 
- not possess/consume any alcoholic beverages 
- not to go upon premises of any bars, taverns or businesses whose primary purpose is the sale of alcohol 
- no contact directly or indirectly with Daniel Wilson Jr., unless approved by Agent or any juvenile Court order 
- not go upon any premises where Daniel Wilson Sr. or Beverly Wilson may be present, unless approved by Agent 
- 43 days credit if revoked 
- 25 hours community service work on all 3 bail jumping charges, concurrent 
- comply with any juvenile Court order regarding minor children 
- maintain absolute sobriety 
Advised of appeal rights.
